parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature tire failure can lead to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Tires develop holes or splits in the sidewall
sudden loss of air pressure
tire blowouts
or tire failure at relatively low mileage (around 5
000 miles).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster needles can cause the driver to lose visibility of critical vehicle information, such as speed, temperature, fuel level, and RPM, which can lead to accidents or unsafe driving conditions.
symptoms: The needles in the instrument cluster become blackened or darkened
making it impossible to read the speedometer
temperature gauge
fuel gauge
and RPM gauge.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially when it occurs at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls when the accelerator pedal is depressed
often in specific operating conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often when attempting to slow down or stop
the engine RPMs increase rapidly
the vehicle does not respond to braking input.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Loss of Brake Pedal Pressure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of brake pedal pressure can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal has no resistance
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the brake warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Hydroplaning and Loss of Vehicle Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Hydroplaning can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle hydroplanes or loses traction on wet roads
the vehicle fishtails or slides sideways
the vehicle is difficult to control
the vehicle crashes or spins out of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected opening of the driver's door while the vehicle is in motion can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The driver's door opens unexpectedly while the vehicle is in motion
often when the automatic window is being rolled down.
